            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h2 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1584628662907--optional--create-a-category-to-manage-multiple-items--and-drop-the-lowest" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1584628662907--optional--create-a-category-to-manage-multiple-items--and-drop-the-lowest" aria-controls="accordion-content-1584628662907--optional--create-a-category-to-manage-multiple-items--and-drop-the-lowest" aria-expanded="false">
                            (optional) Create a category to manage multiple items, and drop the lowest
                        </a>
                    </h2>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1584628662907--optional--create-a-category-to-manage-multiple-items--and-drop-the-lowest" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1584628662907--optional--create-a-category-to-manage-multiple-items--and-drop-the-lowest">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1584628662907 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="fdc6e33e-ede3-4d0e-a1b7-d46701087854" >

    <p>This workflow may be useful If you need to create a scenario where a collection of grades is assessed as a group (i.e. "quizzes are worth 15% total"), and the lowest or highest will be dropped.</p> 
<p>This tutorial assumes that you have already <a href="/content/ryerson/courses/instructors/tutorials/grades/grades-item-create.html">created the grade items</a>, and will proceed with creating a category and moving the grade items into that category.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#fdc6e33e-ede3-4d0e-a1b7-d46701087854");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resImageText section">


























		<div class="thumbnail customStyle1" id="b8c2ed3b-3b35-493d-9163-8f240eafe723">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6">
					
						
<img src="/content/dam/courses/images-screenshots/grades/d2l-grades-reweight-02-create-category.png" alt="Create a new grade category"/>



   
					
